{"parse":{"title":"Dumbing Us Down","pageid":9316488,"revid":784256905,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">Dumbing Us Down <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Dumbing+Us+Down&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BJohn+Taylor+Gatto%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BNew+Society+Publishers%5D%5D&amp;rft.pages=106+%28paperback+and+hardcover%29&amp;rft_id=info:oclcnum/49304855\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:DumbingUsDown_Gatto.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"DumbingUsDown Gatto.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/67/DumbingUsDown_Gatto.jpg/210px-DumbingUsDown_Gatto.jpg\" width=\"210\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/6/67/DumbingUsDown_Gatto.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"257\" data-file-height=\"386\" /></a><div>Cover of the 2002 edition</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/John_Taylor_Gatto\" title=\"John Taylor Gatto\">John Taylor Gatto</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Cover&#160;artist</th><td>\n<a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Diane_McIntosh&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Diane McIntosh (page does not exist)\">Diane McIntosh</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Subject</th><td>\nEducation &amp; Teaching, Current Affairs</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/New_Society_Publishers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New Society Publishers\">New Society Publishers</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\n1992</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Media&#160;type</th><td>\n(<a href=\"/wiki/Paperback\" title=\"Paperback\">paperback</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Hardcover\" title=\"Hardcover\">hardcover</a>)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Pages</th><td>\n106 (paperback and hardcover)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-86571-448-7\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-86571-448-7\">0-86571-448-7</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/OCLC#Identifiers_and_linked_data\" title=\"OCLC\"><abbr title=\"Online Computer Library Center number\">OCLC</abbr></a></th><td>\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/49304855\">49304855</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>Dumbing Us Down: The Hidden Curriculum of Compulsory Schooling</b></i> (<a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/086571231X\" title=\"Special:BookSources/086571231X\">086571231X</a>) is a book by teacher <a href=\"/wiki/John_Taylor_Gatto\" title=\"John Taylor Gatto\">John Taylor Gatto</a>.  It has sold over 200,000 copies<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and consists of a multitude of speeches given by the author. The book proposes that radical change is needed to the American educational system to turn around the negative socialization that children receive.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Dumbing_Us_Down&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span 